Thanks god. pass the CI test finally.
@ashb @feng-tao @kaxil PTAL. Thanks
One question. Why the CI test failed in no reason?

@kaxil This change breaks anything depending on the enum library in Python >3.4 (I'm using 3.6) if Airflow 0.10.2 is installed in that (virtual) environment.

This needs to be reworked to only bring in enum34 if the Python version is < 3.4.

ETA: [enum-compat](https://github.com/jstasiak/enum-compat) will resolve the issue, but the logic could be directly included in setup.py.
